1.1. New WWTP is designed;
1.2. New WWTP is constructed;
1.3. Defect Liability period of the Design-Build Contract of the WWTP successfully completed;
2.1. Joint entity is created and fully functional;
2.2. Transfer of new WWTP to the joint entity is performed and at least 10 years O&M contract is signed

IO 1
Within a reasonable time from the start of the implementation (up to 7 months), a comprehensive framework to ensure adequate caretaking, maintenance and use to all EU funded projects in the field of cultural heritage will be designed, adopted and started its implementation.

IO 2
After the completion and start of implementation of the comprehensive framework for the caretaking, maintenance and use of European Union funded cultural heritage interventions by the TCCH, the Project Steering Committee will define the priority interventions for this objective and the indicators to be applied. Designs for the conservation projects for selected sites based on a list of new cultural heritage sites identified based on the established criteria and approved by the PSC.

IO 3
By the end of the project, depending on funds availability, at least:
-	2  churches will be conserved/completed in the Martinengo cluster;
-	1 site will be conserved/completed in the Paphos cluster;
-	1 church will be conserved in Lefkonoiko/Geçitkale;
-	1 mosque will be conserved/completed in the villages of Agios Ioannis/Ayanni and Agios Nicolaos/Aynikola.

IO 4
By the end of the project:
Visibility/completion ceremonies are organized for each completed project in agreement with the EC and TCCH (at least 6);
At least 6 press releases issued;
At least 2 media visits to the project sites organized;
At least 2 communications update per month is carried out  on social media;
Brochure of the TCCH work is updated and disseminated in agreement with the EC and TCCH, if necessary translated in Greek and Turkish;
At least 1 online and social media campaign developed on the occasion of 18 April International Day for Monuments and Sites with a major event;
At least 2 cultural events are organised in heritage sites where conservation works have been completed (where  and if feasible);
A newsletter is distributed on the achievements of the TCCH and its events;
